                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d469">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/122: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-16T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 16, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 16—2 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Council of Ministers yesterday approved a provision placing Eritrea and
                    Italian Somaliland under a high commissioner for the Colonies of East Africa. An
                    official communiqué published today states that the Minister of Colonies,
                    General de Bono, has resigned in order to take over the post and that the King
                    has appointed Mussolini Minister of Colonies. General de Bono has already left
                    for the Colonies and it is stated that in addition to general administration
                    matters affecting the two colonies he will occupy himself during the present
                    mission with the relations between Italy and Abyssinia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
